* Introduction

Welcome to Chen-Pang He (jdh8)'s experimental Precision Club!  This
document is written in Gert-Jan Paulissen's fork of the Bridge Bidding Markup
Language (BML).

https://github.com/gpaulissen/bml

We use the distribution syntax and abbreviations provided by WBF.

http://www.worldbridge.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Guidetocompletion.pdf

This bidding system is largely based on Meckwell Lite and Standard Modern
Precision.  Changes are made with /Good, Better, Best/ by Jan Eric Larsson and
my improvisation.

- 1C-1D-1H is a relay for 19+ HCP
- 1C-1H is for almost any 8--11 HCP (1C-2S for (4441))
- 1D always shows 4+ diamonds
- 2D is a preempt (Ekren or natural)
- Wild 5-card weak twos
- 2N shows both minors

Notable conventions we use:

- Redwood (Kickback RKCB only for minors)
- Roudi (coded Checkback Stayman)

