* Opening bids

1C = !STR F, 16+ HCP
1D = 4+!d, 11--15 HCP
1H = 5+!h or 4414, 11--15 HCP
1S = 5+!s, 11--15 HCP
1N = 2--4!s 2--4!h 2--5!d 2--5!c or 4414 !dQ, 12--15 HCP
2C = !NAT, 5+!c, 11--15 HCP
2D = !PRE, 4+!s, 4+!h, 4--10 HCP
2M = PRE, 5+#, 4--10 HCP
2N = !UNT, 5+!d, 5+!c, 4--10 HCP
3X = PRE, 7+#, 4--10 HCP
3N = !Gambling, SOL 7+m, 0--1 (partial) stop outside
4C = !Namyats, S-SOL 7+!h, 5.5− NLTC
4D = !Namyats, S-SOL 7+!s, 5.5− NLTC
4M = PRE, good 7+#
4N = !UNT, 6+!d, 6+!c, 11--15 HCP

Our 1D opening always has 4+ diamonds.  We pass BAL 11 HCP without a 5-card
major.

Note that the 5-club option of the Precision 2C must be accompanied with a
4-card major.  With 2245, we open 1NT.  With (31)45, we open 1D.

We replace the Precision 2D opening with more frequent Ekren 2D.  The Precision
2C can describe most of the Precision 2D hands.  The only exception is 4414,
with that distribution we open 1H, 1NT, or pass 11 counts.

** Legal issue of the 2D preempt

If you cannot show both majors via 2D, revert to a natural weak 2D.

2D = PRE, 5+!d, 4--10 HCP

As per ACBL, artificial preempts are only allowed in the Open+ Chart.  Check
your local regulations to see if you can use the Ekren 2D.

http://web2.acbl.org/documentLibrary/about/convention-charts.pdf

** The notrump ladder

- *12--15*: 1N
- *16--18*: 1C-1D-1N
- *19--21*: 1C-1D-1H-1S-1N
- *22+*: 1C-1D-1H-1S-2C-2DH-2N
- *24+*: 1C-1D-1H-1S-2C-2H-3N

* Strong 1C opening

Our first response is the same as Meckwell Lite except that we have more
nonforcing auctions over 1C-1D.

1C-
1D = !NF, 0--7 HCP
1H = !FG, not (4441), 8--11 HCP
1S = !FG, 5+!s, 12+ HCP
1N = !FG, 2--4!s, 2--4!h, 2--5!d, 2--5!c, 12+ HCP
2X = !FG, 5+#, 12+ HCP
2S = !FG PUP, (4441), 8--11 HCP
2N = !FG PUP, (4441), 12+ HCP
3X = !INV, 6+#, 3--7 HCP
4M = PRE, 8+#, 0--4 HCP

